2. When the means uſed for a Peoples Recovery prove Ineffectual. Altho' the Body natural be Incident to divers kinds of Diſeaſes, yet there is generally Balm, & Phyſitians to be had; but in caſe the Phyſitians be Skilful and Faithful, the Means uſed Proper and Suitable againſt the Diſeaſe, and yet take no good Effect, the Diſeaſe ſeems Deadly, and the Wound Incurable. Thus when a People are come to that paſs, that neither Sickneſs, or Health, War or Peace, Scarcity or Plenty, Mercies or Judgments, Corroſives or Lenitives; the unweared endeavours of the Magiſtra ••
〈◊〉 Miniſtry avail, to a Peoples Converſion;
or ſo much as to any conſiderable degree of Reformation; but a People will run over Law and Goſpel, and do that which is right in their own Eyes, in Deſpite of the Powers above and below; they are like the Ground that Yearly brings forth nothing but Briers & Thorns; (Notwithſtanding its drinking in the rains that come oft upon it) and is therefore Rejected nigh unto Curſing, Heb. 6 8 Or like the Vineyard, which after all that was beſtowed upon it, brought forth nothing but Wild Grapes; and was therefore Condemned to be laid waſte, Iſa. 5.6.
